TITLE: Submitting Attestation Request to FDC Hub in Solidity
DESCRIPTION: Defines an internal function `submitAttestationRequest` that orchestrates the submission of an attestation request to the FDC protocol. It retrieves the deployer's private key from environment variables, gets the required fee from `FdcRequestFeeConfigurations`, finds the `FdcHub` contract address via `ContractRegistry`, and then broadcasts a transaction calling `FdcHub.requestAttestation`, sending the `abiEncodedRequest` along with the calculated fee (`msg.value`). Uses Foundry `vm` cheatcodes for environment variables and transaction broadcasting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flare-foundation/developer-hub.git/blob/main/docs/fdc/guides/foundry/payment.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
```solidity title="scrip/fdcExample/Base.s.sol"
function submitAttestationRequest(
 AttestationResponse memory response
) internal {
 uint256 deployerPrivateKey = vm.envUint("PRIVATE_KEY");
 vm.startBroadcast(deployerPrivateKey);
 IFdcRequestFeeConfigurations fdcRequestFeeConfigurations = ContractRegistry
 .getFdcRequestFeeConfigurations();
 uint256 requestFee = fdcRequestFeeConfigurations.getRequestFee(
