TITLE: Submitting an FDC Attestation Request in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This asynchronous TypeScript function `submitAttestationRequest` handles the process of submitting an FDC request. It takes an ABI-encoded request string, retrieves the `FdcHub` instance, calculates the required fee using `getFdcRequestFee`, submits the request to the `FdcHub` contract with the calculated fee, and finally calculates the voting round ID for the submitted request using `calculateRoundId`. It logs the transaction hash and a link to explore the round progress.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flare-foundation/developer-hub.git/blob/main/docs/fdc/guides/hardhat/address-validity.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_8

