TITLE: Posting Proof Requests to DA Layer - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Posts proof requests to the DA Layer using HTTP POST, with JSON payloads. Handles status checks and optional error raising. Depends on fetch and expects properly formatted request bodies. Returns the parsed JSON response from the server or throws if the status is not OK when watchStatus is true.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flare-foundation/developer-hub.git/blob/main/docs/fdc/guides/hardhat/address-validity.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async function postRequestToDALayer(
  url: string,
  request: any,
  watchStatus: boolean = false,
) {
  const response = await fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      //   "X-API-KEY": "",
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify(request),
  });
  if (watchStatus && response.status != 200) {
    throw new Error(
      `Response status is not OK, status ${response.status} ${response.statusText}\n`,
    );
  } else if (watchStatus) {
    console.log("Response status is OK\n");
  }
  return await response.json();
}
```

