TITLE: Retrieving Block Number - Flare Network - Go
DESCRIPTION: Offers a Go example of connecting to Flare Mainnet and retrieving the latest block number using the go-ethereum client package ('github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/rpc'). Requires Go modules, a specified Flare RPC endpoint, and outputs the block number as a uint64.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flare-foundation/developer-hub.git/blob/main/docs/network/0-overview.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
    "context"
    "fmt"
    "log"

    "github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/ethclient"
)

func main() {
    rpcURL := "<FLARE_MAINNET_RPC_URL>"
    client, err := ethclient.Dial(rpcURL)
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
    blockNumber, err := client.BlockNumber(context.Background())
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
    fmt.Printf("Flare block number: %d\n", blockNumber)
}
```

