TITLE: Implementing toUtf8HexString Function for String Encoding in Solidity
DESCRIPTION: Converts a string to UTF8 hex string representation and zero-pads it to 32 bytes. This is required for properly formatting attestation type and source ID parameters for FDC requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/flare-foundation/developer-hub.git/blob/main/docs/fdc/guides/foundry/payment.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
function toUtf8HexString(
 string memory _string
) internal pure returns (string memory) {
 string memory encodedString = toHexString(
 abi.encodePacked(_string)
 );
 uint256 stringLength = bytes(encodedString).length;
 require(stringLength <= 64, "String too long");
 uint256 paddingLength = 64 - stringLength + 2;
 for (uint256 i = 0; i < paddingLength; i++) {
 encodedString = string.concat(encodedString, "0");
 }
 return encodedString;
}
```

